==English==

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[typeface]] or [[font]] whose [[letter]]s [[slant]] or [[lean]] to the right.
# The use of an italic font for emphasis.
#: ''There is no need to put the whole paragraph in '''italics'''.''
# ''usually 'italics' plural but sometimes singular in construction:'' exaggerated intonation or some similar oral speech device by which one or more words is heavily and usually [[affected|affectedly]] emphasized or otherwise given sharp prominence
#:was yapping, her silly voice fraught with ''italics'' -- Margaret Long<p>
#:a woman who has an irritating way of speaking in ''italics'' -- W.J.Locke

